thanks to those who took the trouble, the Joint, the American Joint, we have water today. And today we will arrange for a bath again. Because we had no water for two weeks and we couldn&#39;t take a bath."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4323.340","u": "And so, where did one take water for washing?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4325.755","u": "They have . . . one had . . . with a cart the water was brought."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4328.942","u": "Hm. Go on."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4329.938","u": "And now we will have what to wash the laundry with, and ourselves, too, when one needs."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4335.673","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4335.993","u": "Because it was very terrible. With wood it was also terrible here."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4338.637","u": "Yes? How?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4340.315","u": "Yes. The wood comes out from the subsidy that we receive, the hundred liras. The wood is deducted. A meter of wood, hundred kilos, cost three hundred liras."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4350.064","u": "Hm. What will be done in the winter?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4351.893","u": "That I don&#39;t know. I can imagine the situation when winter comes here, and we [words not clear]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4355.774","u": "And the beds and the blankets? Were these given to you?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4358.762","u": "That was here. That has come already from . . . from the Joint, from UNRRA. That was already here."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4363.320","u": "Yes, but you are not given bed sheets nor towels?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4366.598","u": "That we don&#39;t have. No towels. For soap I have to run a few times till I can get it. That too we don&#39;t have enough of. No soap, and about food you can see yourself."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4376.485","u": "Now tell me, are there not some people who get sent something from America?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4380.409","u": "There are some people, but not in the Kibbutz . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4383.053","u": "Do they get . . ."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4383.856","u": "Those who receive from America, for instance, sit there in the lager and live on it. But in a Kibbutz generally, very . . . only the exact . . . there are some comrades who receive two dollars, or some such in letters. He gives it to the Kibbutz."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4398.995","u": "He gives it to the Kibbutz?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4400.945","u": "Yes! Yes! [With emphasis.] I myself had a friend . . . [interrupted]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4401.748","u": "You mean he cannot posses any money?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4403.426","u": "No. We have no money. I will tell you. Those people who are in a Kibbutz, they say that another comrade is to him the same as himself. There is no difference. Oh, I have a comrade. Let us say he has received five dollars. He has received them in a letter."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4417.883","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4418.324","u": "And a package. So he gave it . . . he had received chocolate. So he said it should be distributed among the children."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4424.891","u": "What?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4425.525","u": "And we . . . so . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4430.113","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4431.851","u": "We live thus."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4432.546","u": "And so, the Kibbutz is really . . . really a [pause], one can say a communistic organization?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4441.588","u": "No!"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4441.920","u": "No, I mean in management. You own everything jointly."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4445.844","u": "Everything jointly. I am telling you . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4447.341","u": "I didn&#39;t mean politically."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4448.929","u": "[Chuckle.] Naturally."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4450.124","u": "Let us say like a cooperative."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4452.026","u": "Oh Yes. We have, for instance, religious [people] here. So we have a kosher kitchen, too."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4457.507","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4457.978","u": "You understand?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4458.690","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4459.203","u": "And we have a common kitchen. If we should all want to eat Kosher like one says, we could not exist. Because a kilo of meat costs three hundred liras, three hundred and fifty liras."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4469.827","u": "A kilo of Kosher meat?"},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4470.551","u": "No, the ordinary . . . cow . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4472.755","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4473.437","u": "When we had gotten the three thousand liras, a kilo of meat was . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4477.240","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4477.439","u": ". . . was two hundred and fifty. And now [it] costs three hundred and fifty. And we always get exactly the three thousand liras. A raise we don&#39;t get."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4485.739","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4486.813","u": "And we have a kosher kitchen in the same manner. Everyone lives collectively. Because if not collectively we cannot exist."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4496.230","u": "Nu, Mr. Wolf, everything was very interesting and everything very important. I think that you have told me a good story."},    {"who": "Isaac Wolf", "start": "4507.143","u": "I am telling you the truth [words not clear]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4508.502","u": "Well, yes, that is what I am saying. You gave me a good report and many a thing has become clear, and many things will become clearer to the people who will study this document. I thank you very much."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4542.804","u": "[In English] This concludes Spool 101, the second spool of Mr. Isaac Wolf who is an officer in one of the Kibbutzim at Camp Tradate, between Como and Milan. Illinois Institute of Technology wire recording. September the 1st, 1946."}        ]
    }
_jsready = true;
var return_val;
switch (String(type)){
        case "transcription":
        return_val = transcription.interview;
        break;
            case "english_translation":
        return_val = english_translation.interview;
        break;
    }
return return_val;
}
function js_ready(){
    return _jsready;
}
